{'reviewer': {'displayName': 'Daniel Correia'}, 'starRating': 'FOUR', 'comment': "(Translated by Google) We camped on the Children's Day holiday, we already imagined it would be full. But not so full...
The place was completely packed! There was a promotion on Day Use, which only increased the demand for the beautiful Camping Chap√©u de Sol!
Despite the huge number of people, the format and distribution of the campsite accommodates so many people. The chalets are well spread out and there are 4 tent areas, all quite large and equipped with toilet sets, and quite far apart from each other. So far away that we only saw two of them when we took a drive before leaving.
The place has 3 swimming pools, playground, games room, courts, sauna, paintball, a replica of an indigenous village and other attractions. Honestly, I don't think we could see everything, so I must be forgetting some things and others are not worth commenting on, like the bocce court, which is well detonated.
And they are still expanding! Soon they will have a fishing lake and another pool that will be beautiful!
The service was super attentive and helpful, we saw people cleaning the camping bathroom at night and the team hired to cheer up the children was great. The downside we found was the restaurant and the system used. As I said, the camping is huge and well distributed, you can hardly have an idea of ​​how many people are inside. Until you want to eat or drink something! At mealtimes the only restaurant is quite full and the queue lasts for a long time! There's no point in arriving early, before they release the only serving line, there's already a considerable queue. What prevents the occurrence of wild west scenes is the very family atmosphere and the quality of the food, in the end everyone left satisfied.
I hope that on big holidays they prioritize guests over Day Use, or otherwise, to avoid overcrowding like Children's Day.

{'reviewer': {'displayName': 'Giovanna Gomes'}, 'starRating': 'THREE', 'comment': "(Translated by Google) I really liked the space, but it lacks details. The chalets are not standardized, there are some larger and others smaller, some with a barbecue and even a pizza oven together and others with just a drum to say it was a barbecue, all paying for the SAME PRICE. The bathroom in my chalet was stinking, with an extremely dirty drain and a wall full of hair, it didn't even have a shower stall, while the bathroom of the couple who were with us was much larger and had a shower stall.
Breakfast is ok, lunch on the first day was pretty bland, on the second day it was much better, and the drink is separate, R$30 for a jug of juice I found quite abusive.
The fishing area is the best part, I found the price for renting the equipment to be very fair. The pools are an ok size, except the heated one which is tiny, I couldn't even get close to it as it was always crowded.

The barbecue is precarious, the night we had a barbecue it rained and as there is no cover it was almost impossible to have a barbecue, but thank God the rain stopped after an average of 1h30m and it was possible to do it quickly, but the lighting is horrible. I felt that the chalets are quite abandoned, there is no maintenance, there are a lot of cobwebs, but as I said, if you are going to use them for bathing and sleeping, you can deal with it. We had a total of 7 sparkling waters and a Juice del Valle and it cost 25 reais. The shower burned out and quickly after contacting reception, they fixed it even though it was 9pm at night. {'reviewer': {'displayName': 'Andre Asprino'}, 'starRating': 'THREE', 'comment': "(Translated by Google) I spent New Year's Eve 2019 at Camping, which I've known since the 1990s. The place is fantastic with lots of green space, very attentive staff and a family atmosphere. The restaurant is good and caters well to visitors, they opened a new one near the lake that I didn't get to use.
The downside is that I noticed that since the 1990s no renovations have been carried out on the site, there is only 1 court for sports and it is in bad shape, the bocce field is already gone, it is abandoned, there are 2 game rooms, 1 of which there is a good pool table and a broken one, in the other room there is an old ping pong table with holes, the electronic arcade and pinball machines have been removed, the children's playground remains the same and without much option, there are 4 swimming pools for adults but small and without any shadow. For those who like it, they play sertanejo music all day long in the leisure areas and at the last volume, which becomes unpleasant for those who don't like it and for those who are already old. Right at the entrance there is a tennis court that has been there I believe since the inauguration, an abandoned and idle space.
In short, a good renovation of the existing areas, a games room with more options, umbrellas or trees around the pools and ambient sound would make this campsite, in my opinion, the best in S√£o Paulo

(Original)
Passei a virada de 2019 no Camping que j√° conhe√ßo desde os anos 90. O lugar √© fant√°stico com muito espa√ßo verde, os funcion√°rios bem atenciosos e ambiente familiar. O restaurante e bom e atende bem aos visitantes, abriram um novo perto do lago que nao cheguei a usar.
O lado ruim √© que notei que desde os anos 90 n√£o foi feita nenhuma reforma no local, s√≥ existe 1 quadra para pr√°tica de esportes e bem judiada, o campo de bocha j√° era, est√° abandonado, tem 2 sal√µes de jogos sendo que  em 1 tem uma mesa de bilhar boa e outra quebrada, no outro sal√£o tem uma mesa de ping pong velha com buracos, as m√°quinas eletr√¥nicas arcade e fliperama foram retiradas, o parque infantil continua o mesmo e sem muita op√ß√£o, existem 4 piscinas adulto por√©m pequenas e sem nenhuma sombra. Pra quem gosta tocam sertanejo o dia inteiro nas √°reas de lazer e no √∫ltimo volume, o que se torna desagrad√°vel para quem n√£o gosta e para quem j√° tem idade avan√ßada. Logo na entrada tem uma quadra de t√™nis que est√° l√° creio que desde a inaugura√ß√£o, um espa√ßo abandonado e ocioso.
Resumindo, uma boa reforma nas √°reas j√° existentes, sal√£o de jogos com mais op√ß√µes, guarda sol ou √°rvores em torno das piscinas e um som ambiente fariam deste camping na minha opini√£o  o melhor de S√£o Paulo", 'createTime': '2020-01-02T18:53:29.988626Z', 'updateTime': '2020-01-02T18:53:29.988626Z', 'name': 'accounts/113838515205835963900/locations/4152719819240239429/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURNMGZPVjBRRRAB'}

{'reviewer': {'displayName': 'Giulian Salgado'}, 'starRating': 'FIVE', 'comment': "(Translated by Google) In 5 years, this was the most incredible trip I took with my family üß°

Anyway, the lunch was delicious, the ideal quantity for the people who were staying, complete breakfast, cold cuts, savory snacks, cakes, Danone, very complete cornflakes
